From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Chris Burr <christopher.burr@cern.ch>
Date: Fri, 28 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: Remove std::_Bit_reference from GaudiPython dictionary

GCC 15 made std::_Bit_reference's default constructor private, causing
ROOT's genreflex-generated dictionary code to fail compilation. This
type is an internal implementation detail of std::vector<bool> and
doesn't need dictionary support for GaudiPython's functionality.
---
 GaudiPython/dict/selection_fragment_main.xml | 1 -
 1 file changed, 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/GaudiPython/dict/selection_fragment_main.xml b/GaudiPython/dict/selection_fragment_main.xml
index 1234567890..abcdefabcd 100644
--- a/GaudiPython/dict/selection_fragment_main.xml
+++ b/GaudiPython/dict/selection_fragment_main.xml
@@ -19,7 +19,6 @@
   <class name    = "std::ostream"/>
   <class name    = "std::basic_stringbuf<char,std::char_traits<char>,std::allocator<char> >" rootmap="false"/>
   <class name    = "std::map<std::basic_string<char>,std::basic_string<char> >"  rootmap="false"/>
-  <class pattern = "std::_Bit_reference*"/>

   <class name    = "std::list<IAlgorithm*>"/>
   <class name    = "std::list<IService*>"/>
--
2.49.0

